    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5}{x+3}-3} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{-3x-4}{x+3}, \left(-\infty ,\infty \right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5}{x+3}-3} 
      \amp = {\frac{5}{x+3}} -\frac{3}{1} \\
      \amp = {\frac{5}{x+3}} -\frac{3}{1} \cdot \frac{(x+3)}{(x+3)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{5}{x+3}-\frac{3\mathopen{}\left(x+3\right)}{x+3}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{5-3\mathopen{}\left(x+3\right)}{x+3}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{5-3x-9}{x+3}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-3x-4}{x+3}, \left(-\infty ,\infty \right)}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
